<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="501" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1425,2026]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1497,1522]" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head with dorsum black and orange-white spots anteriorly and another medially to antennae base. Pronotum dark brown with pair of pale yellow stripes anteriorly and laterally to middle lobe. Border of medial and apex of lateral portions of posterior prothorax lobe pale yellow. Median portion straight, separated from lateral portions by deep incision at each side (
<figureCitation box="[590,674,1605,1630]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,211,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[159,1428,127,1941]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Prothorax in dorsal view: in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (8); P. martinezi female, holotype, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (9); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype, Porto Acre (10); P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (11); P. pronoti female, holotype (12); P. quadratum sp. nov. male, holotype (13)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376929/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
); lateral portions with apex rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1097,1181,1605,1630]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,211,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[159,1428,127,1941]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Prothorax in dorsal view: in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (8); P. martinezi female, holotype, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (9); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype, Porto Acre (10); P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (11); P. pronoti female, holotype (12); P. quadratum sp. nov. male, holotype (13)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376929/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Mesepisternum (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 19" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1903,1926]" captionTargetBox="[195,1401,236,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1883]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 19. Pterothorax in lateral view: in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (14); P. martinezi female, holotype (15); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype (16); P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (17); P. pronoti female, holotype (18); P. quadratum male, holotype (19)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376930/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) black with antehumeral grayish-yellow stripe occupying whole extension of sclerite. Mesepimeron dark brown with grayish-yellow stripe not reaching lower part of sclerite. Metapleuron (
<figureCitation box="[1034,1118,1677,1702]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 19" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1903,1926]" captionTargetBox="[195,1401,236,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1883]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 19. Pterothorax in lateral view: in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (14); P. martinezi female, holotype (15); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype (16); P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (17); P. pronoti female, holotype (18); P. quadratum male, holotype (19)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376930/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) whitish yellow with black stripe adjacent to metapleural suture occupying dorsal ¾ of sclerite. Venter of pterothorax whitish yellow, with narrow middle dark stripe occupying its anterior ½. It is impossible to know whether this stripe reaches the posterior part of the venter, because it is damaged. Supplementary tooth of tarsal claws absent. Wings dominantly hyaline with apical area milky-white reaching a row of cells posterior to RP1. Pseudostigma in both wings weakly indicate pale yellow color (
<figureCitation box="[472,616,1857,1882]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 36" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1974,1997]" captionTargetBox="[194,1404,194,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[156,1430,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 36. P. pronoti reproduced from Machado &amp; Lacerda (2016), female holotype, Fw non saturated (33), saturated (34), Hw non saturated (35), saturated (36)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376934/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">Figs. 33, 35</figureCitation>
). At high saturation, the color of apical area changes; the white color becomes pale blue and the pseudostigma appears very evident, yellow, with six cells in Fw and eight in Hw (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 36" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1974,1997]" captionTargetBox="[194,1404,194,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[156,1430,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 36. P. pronoti reproduced from Machado &amp; Lacerda (2016), female holotype, Fw non saturated (33), saturated (34), Hw non saturated (35), saturated (36)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376934/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">Figs. 34, 36</figureCitation>
). Costal vein becomes orange and RA to RP1 yellow (
<figureCitation box="[854,995,1929,1954]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 36" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1974,1997]" captionTargetBox="[194,1404,194,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[156,1430,151,1965]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 36. P. pronoti reproduced from Machado &amp; Lacerda (2016), female holotype, Fw non saturated (33), saturated (34), Hw non saturated (35), saturated (36)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376934/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="501">Figs. 34, 36</figureCitation>
). Abdomen dominantly brown. Cercus dark, with apex rounded. Ovipositor (stylus lacking) reaching posteriorly about level of hind border of S10.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
