<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="502" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,693,1978]" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,765,790]" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Etymology.</emphasis>
From Latin 
<emphasis box="[483,673,765,790]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">quadratum-a-um</emphasis>
, quadrate, an allusion to the shape of its penis segment 
<quantity box="[1328,1373,765,790]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="9" pageNumber="502" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
ectal view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="502" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,693,1978]" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,597,837,862]" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">
Description of the male 
<typeStatus box="[487,592,837,862]" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[605,665,837,862]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Head</emphasis>
. Labium whitish yellow, base of mandible and genae bluish yellow, anteclypeus and postclypeus grayish blue, antefrons brownish. Upper part of head black with metallic green luster. Postocular lobe and occipital crest yellow. Rear of head whitish yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,693,1978]" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">
<emphasis box="[199,280,945,970]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Thorax</emphasis>
. Prothorax: pronotum black. Anterior lobe with pair of pale oblong transverse spots. Middle lobe with large pale marking dilated posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[592,676,981,1006]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,211,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[159,1428,127,1941]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Prothorax in dorsal view: in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (8); P. martinezi female, holotype, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (9); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype, Porto Acre (10); P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (11); P. pronoti female, holotype (12); P. quadratum sp. nov. male, holotype (13)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376929/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Posterior lobe bordered with yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1122,1206,981,1006]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,211,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[159,1428,127,1941]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Prothorax in dorsal view: in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (8); P. martinezi female, holotype, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (9); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype, Porto Acre (10); P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (11); P. pronoti female, holotype (12); P. quadratum sp. nov. male, holotype (13)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376929/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Propleuron yellow with black markings (
<figureCitation box="[420,512,1017,1042]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,211,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[159,1428,127,1941]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Prothorax in dorsal view: in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (8); P. martinezi female, holotype, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (9); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype, Porto Acre (10); P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (11); P. pronoti female, holotype (12); P. quadratum sp. nov. male, holotype (13)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376929/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Pterothorax: mesepisternum (
<figureCitation box="[888,978,1017,1042]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 19" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1903,1926]" captionTargetBox="[195,1401,236,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1883]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 19. Pterothorax in lateral view: in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (14); P. martinezi female, holotype (15); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype (16); P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (17); P. pronoti female, holotype (18); P. quadratum male, holotype (19)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376930/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) black with middorsal carina yellow, antehumeral yellow stripe reduced to triangular marking at about 1/3 of sclerite. Posthumeral yellow stripe not reaching lower part of sclerite. Mesepimeron black. Metapleuron yellow with black stripe along metapleural suture. Venter with anterior triangular and posterior subcylindrical black spots (
<figureCitation box="[1040,1125,1125,1150]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 24" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[280,1335,276,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1924]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 24. Venter in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (20); P. martinezi female, holotype (21); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype (22). P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (23); P. quadratum sp. nov. male, holotype (24)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376931/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,693,1978]" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">
<emphasis box="[199,266,1162,1185]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Wings</emphasis>
. Fw hyaline with light brown pseudostigma, with six cells. Hw with large apical area bluish white reaching RP2; pseudostigma blue with eight cells (
<figureCitation box="[725,809,1197,1222]" captionStart="FIGURES 29 – 32" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[207,1393,228,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1930]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 29 – 32. P. minimum, sp. nov. male, holotype, Fw non saturated (29), saturated (30). P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype, Hw non saturated (31). P. quadratum sp. nov. male, holotype, Hw non saturated (32)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376933/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
). At high saturation, bluish white area becomes whitish blue, surrounded by blue and pseudostigma more intensely blue. Venation: Px in Fw 31, in Hw 33, RP 
<quantity box="[1303,1346,1233,1258]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="9" pageNumber="502" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
Fw and in Hw originating at Px 11. IR1 originating at Px 
<quantity box="[714,772,1269,1294]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.064" pageId="9" pageNumber="502" unit="in" value="16.0">16 in</quantity>
Fw, at Px 
<quantity box="[894,952,1269,1294]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.556" pageId="9" pageNumber="502" unit="in" value="14.0">14 in</quantity>
Hw. RP2 branching from RP at about half distance from subnodus to tip of wing. Petiolation originates distal to CuP by two times length of CuP in Fw and three times in Hw.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,693,1978]" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">
<emphasis box="[199,252,1378,1401]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Legs</emphasis>
. Femora with proximal 1/3 yellow, distally black on extensor surface and yellow on flexural surface. Tibiae with extensor surface yellow and flexural surface black. Tarsi black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,693,1978]" box="[199,892,1449,1474]" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">
<emphasis box="[199,305,1449,1474]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Abdomen</emphasis>
. S1–10 dorsally black, laterally yellow. Cerci black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,693,1978]" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,460,1485,1510]" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Structural characters</emphasis>
. Median and lateral portions of posterior prothoracic lobe not separated. Posterior border slightly convex (
<figureCitation box="[422,506,1521,1546]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 13" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1930,1953]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,211,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[159,1428,127,1941]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 13. Prothorax in dorsal view: in P. astictum male, Itatiaia, Rio de Janeiro (8); P. martinezi female, holotype, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (9); P. humaita sp. nov. male, holotype, Porto Acre (10); P. minimum sp. nov. male, holotype (11); P. pronoti female, holotype (12); P. quadratum sp. nov. male, holotype (13)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376929/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Cleft of anterior lamina shaped as ogival Gothic arch (
<figureCitation box="[1149,1234,1521,1546]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 41" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[254,1339,240,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[165,1422,141,1955]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 41. Genitalia of second segment in P. astictum, Tinguá, Rio de Janeiro (37); P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (38); P. humaita sp. nov., holotype (39); P. minimum sp. nov., holotype (40); P. quadratum sp. nov., holotype (41)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376935/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
). Anterior hamuli with ear-like basal plate. Posterior hamuli with apex curved anteromedially (
<figureCitation box="[1017,1101,1557,1582]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 41" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[254,1339,240,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[165,1422,141,1955]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 41. Genitalia of second segment in P. astictum, Tinguá, Rio de Janeiro (37); P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (38); P. humaita sp. nov., holotype (39); P. minimum sp. nov., holotype (40); P. quadratum sp. nov., holotype (41)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376935/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
). Distal portion of batilliform lamina very small, apex sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[574,659,1593,1618]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 41" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[254,1339,240,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[165,1422,141,1955]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 41. Genitalia of second segment in P. astictum, Tinguá, Rio de Janeiro (37); P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz (38); P. humaita sp. nov., holotype (39); P. minimum sp. nov., holotype (40); P. quadratum sp. nov., holotype (41)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376935/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
). Penis segment 
<quantity box="[855,900,1593,1618]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="9" pageNumber="502" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
ectal view subquadrate with small tongue-like apical lobe and tuft of spines at anterolateral angle (
<figureCitation box="[745,831,1629,1654]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 51" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[264,1319,197,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[204,1372,153,1898]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 51. Penis of P. astictum, Tinguá, Rio de Janeiro, in ectal (42) and lateral (43) views; P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz, in ectal (44) and lateral (45) views. P. humaita sp. nov. in ectal (46) and lateral (47) views; P. minimum sp. nov. in ectal (48) and lateral (49) views; P. quadratum sp. nov. in ectal (50) and lateral views (51)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376936/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
); in lateral view with medial and distal tuft of spines (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,1665,1690]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 51" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[264,1319,197,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[204,1372,153,1898]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 51. Penis of P. astictum, Tinguá, Rio de Janeiro, in ectal (42) and lateral (43) views; P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz, in ectal (44) and lateral (45) views. P. humaita sp. nov. in ectal (46) and lateral (47) views; P. minimum sp. nov. in ectal (48) and lateral (49) views; P. quadratum sp. nov. in ectal (50) and lateral views (51)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376936/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
). Penis segment 2 with large tuft of spines near commissure (
<figureCitation box="[948,1087,1665,1690]" captionStart="FIGURES 42 – 51" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[264,1319,197,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[204,1372,153,1898]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 42 – 51. Penis of P. astictum, Tinguá, Rio de Janeiro, in ectal (42) and lateral (43) views; P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz, in ectal (44) and lateral (45) views. P. humaita sp. nov. in ectal (46) and lateral (47) views; P. minimum sp. nov. in ectal (48) and lateral (49) views; P. quadratum sp. nov. in ectal (50) and lateral views (51)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376936/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Figs. 50–51</figureCitation>
). Hind border of S 
<quantity box="[1300,1359,1665,1690]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="9" pageNumber="502" unit="in" value="10.0">10 in</quantity>
dorsal view with medial concavity (
<figureCitation box="[498,587,1701,1726]" captionStart="FIGURES 54 – 61" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1836,1859]" captionTargetBox="[208,1385,237,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1815]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 54 – 61. Male cercus in P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz, in dorsal (54) and lateral (55) views; P. humaita sp. nov., holotype, in dorsal (56) and lateral (57) views; P. minimum sp. nov. in dorsal (58) and lateral (59) views; P. quadratum sp. nov. in dorsal (60) and lateral (61) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376938/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
); in lateral view with distal ½ elevated (
<figureCitation box="[1078,1167,1701,1726]" captionStart="FIGURES 54 – 61" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1836,1859]" captionTargetBox="[208,1385,237,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1815]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 54 – 61. Male cercus in P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz, in dorsal (54) and lateral (55) views; P. humaita sp. nov., holotype, in dorsal (56) and lateral (57) views; P. minimum sp. nov. in dorsal (58) and lateral (59) views; P. quadratum sp. nov. in dorsal (60) and lateral (61) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376938/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
). Cerci in lateral view cylindrical, with distal 1/3 tapering and directed ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[810,894,1737,1762]" captionStart="FIGURES 54 – 61" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1836,1859]" captionTargetBox="[208,1385,237,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1815]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 54 – 61. Male cercus in P. martinezi, Bolívia, Santa Cruz, in dorsal (54) and lateral (55) views; P. humaita sp. nov., holotype, in dorsal (56) and lateral (57) views; P. minimum sp. nov. in dorsal (58) and lateral (59) views; P. quadratum sp. nov. in dorsal (60) and lateral (61) views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376938/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="502">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
). In dorsal view, distally convergent (
